# Project Constraints

> This file records hard constraints for THIS project.
> Constraints are non-negotiable rules that the LLM must never violate.
> Add the pre-LLM pipeline command for this project at the bottom.

---

## How to add a constraint

```markdown
- [what is forbidden or required] — [reason]
```

---

## Universal Constraints (inherited from base-standards.mdc)

- No TODO or FIXME in committed code without a corresponding ticket
- All public APIs must have documentation
- Error handling must be explicit — no silent swallowing
- Commits must be atomic and descriptive
- English only in code, comments, and commit messages

